==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-taint.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪnt|-eɪnt]]

===Etymology 1===
From {{F.}} [[atteinte]] (a blow, bit, stroke). Compare with [[attaint]].

====Noun====
'''taint'''

# A [[thrust]] with a [[lance]], which fails of its intended [[effect]].
# An [[injury]] done to a [[lance]] in an encounter, without its being broken; also, a breaking of a lance in an encounter in a [[dishonorable]] or unscientific manner.

===Etymology 2===
From {{L.}} [[tingere]], [[tinctum]] via {{F.}} [[teint]] (past participle of [[teindre]] to dye, to tinge)

====Noun====
'''taint'''

# A [[contamination]], [[decay]] or [[putrefaction]], especially in [[food]]
# A mark of [[disgrace]], especially on one's [[character]]

====Transitive verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To [[contaminate]] or [[corrupt]] something with an external [[agent]], either [[physically]] or [[morally]].
# To [[spoil]] food by contamination.

